IMPORTANT — THIRD-PARTY COMPONENT LICENSES
===========================================

This repository contains only orchestration and pipeline glue code. Running the
full pipeline requires installing third-party software and model weights that are
governed by their own licenses, some of which impose additional restrictions:

  PyMeshLab         GPL-3.0       https://github.com/cnr-isti-vclab/PyMeshLab
  Blender / bpy     GPL-2.0+      https://www.blender.org/about/license/
  nvdiffrast        NVIDIA Source Code License (non-commercial research only)
                                  https://github.com/NVlabs/nvdiffrast/blob/main/LICENSE.txt
  FLUX.1-dev        FLUX.1-dev Non-Commercial License (research/personal use only)
                                  https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/blob/main/LICENSE.md

Files in this repository that directly import PyMeshLab (src/stage3_mesh_optimization.py)
or Blender/bpy (src/stage4_assemble_final.py) are consequently subject to the GPL-3.0
and GPL-2.0-or-later licenses respectively when used as part of a combined work.

Due to the FLUX.1-dev and nvdiffrast licenses, THE COMPLETE RUNNING PIPELINE IS
RESTRICTED TO NON-COMMERCIAL, RESEARCH AND PERSONAL USE ONLY.

Other third-party components used by this pipeline and their licenses:
  TRELLIS.2         MIT           https://github.com/microsoft/TRELLIS
  UniRig (Puppeteer) MIT          https://github.com/VAST-AI-Research/UniRig
  SAMPart3D         MIT           https://github.com/Pointcept/SAMPart3D
  BiRefNet (rembg)  MIT           https://github.com/ZhengPeng7/BiRefNet
  FlexGEMM          MIT           https://github.com/JeffreyXiang/FlexGEMM
  CuMesh            MIT           https://github.com/JeffreyXiang/CuMesh
  DINOv2            Apache-2.0   https://github.com/facebookresearch/dinov2
  FLUX.1-schnell    Apache-2.0   https://github.com/black-forest-labs/flux

